WEBVTT

00:52.440 --> 00:55.270
TIM JENKIN: By the time Stephen and I graduated in '73,

00:55.320 --> 00:58.580
half of South Africa
was in flames.

01:02.150 --> 01:04.810
The police were shooting
black kids like rabbits

01:04.850 --> 01:08.070
whilst the other half
sipped piÃ±a coladas

01:08.110 --> 01:10.020
on their whites-only beaches.

01:12.860 --> 01:15.210
Growing up under apartheid

01:15.250 --> 01:18.390
meant the segregation of people by the colour of their skin.

01:20.380 --> 01:21.900
And as our eyes opened,

01:21.950 --> 01:24.600
the naked reality of apartheid
stood before us.

01:24.650 --> 01:26.180
I was born like this!

01:26.220 --> 01:29.350
I'm not ashamed to be a Saffer.
Ask in the eyes of God!

01:30.960 --> 01:34.000
What we'd always accepted,
we would now reject.

01:34.050 --> 01:36.830
[ANGRY SHOUTING]

01:36.880 --> 01:40.630
[ALL CHANT]

01:40.670 --> 01:43.720
We didn't want a life built on lies and indifference.

01:43.760 --> 01:45.150
[SCREAMING]

01:45.190 --> 01:47.190
We wanted to join
the ongoing struggle

01:47.240 --> 01:49.680
for a democratic and free
South Africa

01:49.720 --> 01:52.640
not based on
racial discrimination.

02:17.530 --> 02:20.190
But unless we got up from our privileged white lives

02:20.230 --> 02:23.970
and did something,
our words were meaningless.

02:27.100 --> 02:30.620
What we chose to do was
the most radical of all things

02:30.670 --> 02:34.060
and without doubt
the most explosive.

02:34.110 --> 02:36.240
[CLOCK TICKS]

02:37.900 --> 02:40.340
[CLOCK TICKS]

02:50.300 --> 02:52.860
[TICKING CONTINUES]

03:11.320 --> 03:13.930
[TICKING CONTINUES]

03:21.460 --> 03:23.590
[TICKING]

03:35.560 --> 03:37.910
[TICKING]

03:47.570 --> 03:49.790
[ALL EXCLAIM]

03:51.400 --> 03:54.750
We joined the prohibited
African National Congress...

03:59.280 --> 04:01.060
..and ran
anti-apartheid missions

04:01.110 --> 04:03.980
alongside our black and Asian
brothers and sisters,

04:04.030 --> 04:07.560
spreading the news that freedom and equality for all races

04:07.590 --> 04:11.290
should be fought for
at all costs.

04:11.340 --> 04:12.870
- Let's go!
- Aren't we going to watch?

04:12.900 --> 04:14.290
No, Stephen, we don't
have time for this, OK?

04:14.340 --> 04:15.820
- Let's just...
- [BOOM!]

04:20.830 --> 04:22.660
They're closing in on us.

04:26.700 --> 04:28.870
[TYRES SCREECH]

04:28.920 --> 04:30.870
MAN: Hey, you!
Stay where you are!

04:30.920 --> 04:32.440
[BOOM!]

04:35.670 --> 04:38.460
And the costs were greater
than either of us imagined.

04:40.320 --> 04:42.280
[JAIL DOOR SLAMS, LOCKS]

04:56.860 --> 04:58.510
[CHAINS CLANK]

04:58.560 --> 05:01.520
I've got you the money. Don't
let them catch you with it.

05:01.560 --> 05:03.120
They will add another 12 years
to your life.

05:03.170 --> 05:04.860
- Make sure you don't appeal.
- I won't.

05:04.910 --> 05:06.430
I'm not begging
some fascist bastard judge

05:06.480 --> 05:07.700
to come take pity on us.

05:07.740 --> 05:09.430
WOMAN: Give it to me.

05:15.880 --> 05:18.400
Whatever happens in there,
don't give up.

05:18.450 --> 05:20.020
I won't.

05:21.410 --> 05:23.370
[DOOR SLAMS]

05:23.410 --> 05:25.070
Go, go, go. I love you.

05:54.790 --> 05:56.360
OK.

06:05.190 --> 06:06.750
[GRUNTS]

06:10.720 --> 06:12.330
[SQUELCH!]

06:12.370 --> 06:15.150
- [QUIET CHATTER]
- MAN: All rise.

06:17.640 --> 06:22.870
The Republic of South Africa v.
Timothy Jenkin and Stephen Lee.

06:30.650 --> 06:33.340
JUDGE: My commendation
to the prosecution.

06:33.390 --> 06:36.000
A very well put case.

06:36.050 --> 06:39.490
The retrieval of
17 custom-built devices

06:39.530 --> 06:43.710
for 26 separate bombings
is no small thing.

06:45.270 --> 06:48.530
But laying out
the most pernicious aspects

06:48.580 --> 06:52.150
of this ANC ideology...

06:52.190 --> 06:56.150
..that all races are equal
and all this sort of thing

06:56.200 --> 06:59.380
has been the strongest part
of your case.

06:59.420 --> 07:02.380
And if I'm to understand it
correctly,

07:02.420 --> 07:06.030
one of the defendants' fathers
is an eminent pharmacologist

07:06.080 --> 07:09.430
and the other a scholar
in the humanities.

07:10.860 --> 07:12.990
This country raised you.

07:15.220 --> 07:17.180
It gave birth to you

07:17.220 --> 07:21.360
and it provided
all your worldly needs.

07:21.400 --> 07:25.100
And this is how
you choose to repay it?

07:27.880 --> 07:30.360
The State of South Africa
now tells you

07:30.410 --> 07:34.240
the price you will pay
in return.

07:34.280 --> 07:36.240
And so,

07:36.280 --> 07:42.590
defendant number one and chief
bomb maker, Timothy Jenkin,

07:42.640 --> 07:44.820
you are sentenced
to imprisonment

07:44.860 --> 07:47.250
for a total of 12 years.

07:47.290 --> 07:49.590
[GALLERY MURMURS]

07:49.640 --> 07:53.420
And defendant number two,
the accomplice, Stephen Lee,

07:53.470 --> 07:55.380
you are sentenced
to imprisonment

07:55.430 --> 07:58.210
for a total of eight years.

07:59.260 --> 08:00.690
Sentences are to commence

08:00.740 --> 08:04.130
at Pretoria Political Prison
for White Males.

08:05.750 --> 08:08.010
So...that's that.

08:09.660 --> 08:11.360
MAN: All rise.

08:17.840 --> 08:19.360
[SOBS SOFTLY]

08:20.930 --> 08:22.450
Sit there!

08:23.720 --> 08:25.670
[GUARD WALKS OFF]

08:26.980 --> 08:29.200
[PIGEON COOS]

08:48.660 --> 08:50.270
[BANG!]

08:58.150 --> 08:59.890
Shit! Don't shoot! Don't shoot!

09:01.190 --> 09:02.800
Let's talk about this,
man, alright?

09:02.850 --> 09:04.510
Let's talk. Let me esca...

09:21.910 --> 09:24.440
GUARD: [POUNDS ON WALL]
Keep your mouth shut in there!

09:24.480 --> 09:27.180
- Alright?!
- [ENGINE STARTS]

09:27.220 --> 09:29.750
- How's it?
- How's it?

10:15.960 --> 10:18.400
MAN: At last, the leaflet
bombers are here, hmm?

10:18.440 --> 10:20.090
And after all your fancy tricks,

10:20.140 --> 10:22.960
you're reduced to jumping
from windows like rats, huh?

10:23.010 --> 10:24.880
Hey!

10:24.930 --> 10:28.200
No-one forced you to traitor
your country and your race!

10:29.150 --> 10:30.810
You are the white Mandela.

10:32.940 --> 10:34.900
You are the most deluded
of them all.

10:37.940 --> 10:39.500
Van der Merwe!

10:41.160 --> 10:42.720
Read it!

10:42.770 --> 10:45.810
"No pens, no radio,
no newspapers.

10:45.860 --> 10:47.380
"No political conversation.

10:47.430 --> 10:50.570
"No parcels larger than
the size of a 6" x 4" envelope.

10:50.610 --> 10:53.270
"Visitors once per month,
subject to state vetting.

10:53.300 --> 10:56.260
"And there is to be
no sexual activity of any kind

10:56.310 --> 10:58.580
"anywhere on the premises."

10:58.610 --> 11:00.390
Here! Step on the line.

11:02.660 --> 11:04.660
Step over the line.

11:04.710 --> 11:06.580
Disengage the grille door.

11:10.280 --> 11:12.370
Move.

11:16.680 --> 11:18.550
Up to the line.

11:26.900 --> 11:28.420
Proceed.

11:34.350 --> 11:35.660
Move.

11:35.690 --> 11:37.170
[GUNS CLICK]

11:43.960 --> 11:47.140
[PRISONERS CHATTER,
SHOUT AND WHISTLE]

11:51.930 --> 11:53.590
Come on, move!

12:01.020 --> 12:02.670
In.

12:14.210 --> 12:16.080
39378.

12:17.870 --> 12:19.570
In.

12:23.390 --> 12:25.040
Turn.

12:26.700 --> 12:28.960
[SHACKLES CLICK]

12:29.010 --> 12:30.800
Move!

12:49.330 --> 12:51.290
Alright, pube lice!

12:51.340 --> 12:54.170
Lights out 11:00,
morning bell 5:00,

12:54.210 --> 12:56.390
breakfast 7:30.

12:56.430 --> 12:58.700
I like my cells
clean as a plate.

12:58.730 --> 13:02.250
Remember that and you'll live
a long and prosperous life.

13:02.300 --> 13:05.520
Now...total silence!

13:23.590 --> 13:25.550
[KNOCK ON WALL]

13:31.590 --> 13:35.160
[KNOCK ON WALL]

13:41.820 --> 13:43.730
[STEPHEN REPEATS PATTERN]

13:55.620 --> 13:57.410
[DOG BARKS IN DISTANCE]

13:57.440 --> 14:00.970
[WATER DRIPS]

14:09.670 --> 14:12.720
[BELL RINGS]

14:19.640 --> 14:21.590
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

14:22.860 --> 14:24.470
[DOOR UNLOCKS]

14:34.610 --> 14:36.170
Step away from the grille.

14:50.760 --> 14:52.770
Best bloody kip in years.

14:52.800 --> 14:54.580
I could get used to this.

14:54.630 --> 14:56.500
VAN DER MERWE: Fall out!

14:56.550 --> 14:58.640
Idiot.

14:58.680 --> 15:00.630
Go. Walk. Walk!

15:05.430 --> 15:07.820
GUARD: Alright, guys,
move along. Move along.

15:27.270 --> 15:30.710
Alright, quieten down.
Let's keep it down, guys.

15:30.760 --> 15:32.890
[QUIETLY] Walk. Walk.

15:32.930 --> 15:34.620
Go on.

15:35.980 --> 15:37.590
Sit.

15:38.550 --> 15:40.070
Thank you.

15:40.110 --> 15:41.590
Don't sit there.

15:41.640 --> 15:43.470
We are segregated, my friend.

15:43.510 --> 15:45.860
They wear blue shirts
for a reason.

15:45.900 --> 15:48.330
Unless you want to sit
next to a murderer.

15:48.380 --> 15:50.730
No. This is...this is good.

15:55.080 --> 15:56.730
[CLEARS THROAT] Kitson.

15:56.780 --> 15:58.950
[MEN ALL COUGH]

16:02.400 --> 16:04.660
Alright, quiet down, huh?

16:06.530 --> 16:08.400
TIM: What was that?

16:10.360 --> 16:12.050
Can I join you, gentlemen?

16:12.100 --> 16:13.920
- Can I...?
- Please.

16:13.970 --> 16:16.270
We've heard about you two.

16:16.320 --> 16:19.190
- We've heard about you.
- Yeah. It's...it's an honour.

16:19.240 --> 16:20.940
How many years?

16:20.980 --> 16:24.290
Eight for me. 12 for him.

16:24.330 --> 16:27.110
TIM: Ja, but we don't plan
on staying that long.

16:29.120 --> 16:30.990
Hold on to that anger.

16:31.030 --> 16:34.550
It reminds you there's
another world outside all this.

16:35.470 --> 16:37.210
[CLATTERING IN DISTANCE]

16:38.780 --> 16:40.730
- [CLATTERING]
- [MEN LAUGH]

16:40.780 --> 16:42.780
VAN DER MERWE:
Nobody said stop. Move!

16:42.830 --> 16:45.270
- MAN: Calm down, now.
- [TROLLEY CLATTERS]

16:45.310 --> 16:47.790
Oh, dear. Oh, dear.

16:47.830 --> 16:51.830
Ladies, we're going to call
this one Potluck.

16:51.880 --> 16:53.400
[ALL LAUGH]

16:53.450 --> 16:55.280
One for each slop, my friend.

16:56.450 --> 16:58.200
[POTLUCK SCREAMS]

16:58.230 --> 16:59.750
- [THUMP!]
- [POTLUCK SCREAMS]

16:59.800 --> 17:01.710
[MEN CALL OUT]

17:01.760 --> 17:04.200
Damned bastards!

17:05.940 --> 17:08.680
VAN DER MERWE:
Come on. Get it over there.

17:09.770 --> 17:11.340
Good boy.

17:11.380 --> 17:13.860
[PRISONERS LAUGH, HECKLE]

17:14.770 --> 17:17.070
[MEN PUFF]

17:19.650 --> 17:21.870
Something's weighing you down,
I think.

17:21.910 --> 17:23.650
Are you packing?

17:25.090 --> 17:27.140
You can tell by the way you run
you've got at least

17:27.180 --> 17:29.570
a bottle of beer
and some glasses up there.

17:29.610 --> 17:32.740
Cigar tubes. 360 rand.

17:34.400 --> 17:36.750
Expensive tastes.

17:36.790 --> 17:39.050
Let me give you the guided tour.

17:40.840 --> 17:44.230
In case you're wondering,
it's 20 foot high.

17:44.280 --> 17:49.150
The barbed wire's flailed so
it traps right under your skin.

17:49.200 --> 17:52.380
Searchlights.
On from sundown to sunrise.

17:52.420 --> 17:54.820
Covers every inch of the yard.

17:54.860 --> 17:58.470
Boers with guns
from lockup till dawn.

17:58.510 --> 18:01.640
There's nothing they'd like more
than to pump holes into you.

18:06.040 --> 18:09.560
And tunnels in any direction,

18:09.610 --> 18:12.100
they just lead you back
onto prison property.

18:12.130 --> 18:15.790
Apart from that wall.
It lines a public street.

18:24.150 --> 18:25.940
I knew a chap one time.

18:25.970 --> 18:29.230
No matter how hard he tried,
he couldn't get his money out.

18:29.280 --> 18:31.890
And the whole thing
got infected.

18:31.940 --> 18:35.160
The point I'm making is,
everybody comes in here going

18:35.200 --> 18:37.370
they're gonna break out of here
by next week.

18:39.160 --> 18:41.640
We are prisoners of conscience.

18:41.690 --> 18:43.690
So it's different for us.

18:44.730 --> 18:46.730
But we're prisoners of war.

18:49.040 --> 18:51.910
All the same,
I've got a hiding place.

18:51.960 --> 18:53.660
I'll keep it safe for you.

18:53.700 --> 18:56.050
Get it out before
it rots you inside.

19:09.970 --> 19:13.280
He pours cold water on
any poor bastard with a plan.

19:14.280 --> 19:16.580
I don't talk to him.

19:16.630 --> 19:18.720
So there have been attempts?

19:18.770 --> 19:20.560
Some go a little...

19:22.900 --> 19:26.160
..some a little more,
but no-one go out.

19:26.210 --> 19:28.910
Always a first time.

19:28.950 --> 19:30.730
That's my thoughts exactly.

19:30.780 --> 19:32.700
It is a duty for us.

19:32.740 --> 19:35.830
I don't do this "prisoner
of conscience" bullshit.

19:35.870 --> 19:39.090
If you're having a plan,
I join you.

19:39.130 --> 19:40.430
GUARD: [OVER P.A.] Time!

19:40.480 --> 19:41.960
The cell is a concrete tomb.

19:42.010 --> 19:43.930
Only way out is
through the grille.

19:43.970 --> 19:45.750
You tell me when
you have something.

19:45.790 --> 19:48.050
Back to your cells!

20:08.470 --> 20:10.340
- [GRUNTS]
- [PLOP!]

20:16.300 --> 20:18.910
TIM: Every prison has its doyen,

20:18.960 --> 20:21.920
and for us politicals
it was Denis Goldberg.

20:23.660 --> 20:25.530
He'd been given
four life sentences

20:25.570 --> 20:27.740
for trying to overthrow
the apartheid government

20:27.790 --> 20:29.400
by violent revolution...

20:30.970 --> 20:33.630
..in the same trial
as Mandela and Sisulu.

20:38.110 --> 20:39.940
He was royalty.

21:22.110 --> 21:24.510
[DOOR CLANKS OPEN]

21:29.110 --> 21:31.370
[KEYS JANGLE]

21:34.550 --> 21:39.250
For many nights, I sat on
my bed and stared at the lock.

21:42.910 --> 21:45.350
I tried a hundred ideas
in my mind...

21:46.520 --> 21:50.170
..and then I tried
a hundred more.

21:55.100 --> 22:01.110
It sat there staring back at me every single night.

22:04.110 --> 22:07.160
And then it dawned on me.

22:07.200 --> 22:09.290
You don't have to know
everything.

22:11.110 --> 22:12.590
You only have to know enough.

22:12.640 --> 22:14.340
GUARD: Now, quiet!

22:14.380 --> 22:18.120
You start with what you know
and you work backwards.

23:27.930 --> 23:29.980
TIM: Hey. We've got something.

23:31.890 --> 23:34.110
We're not doing anything
that involves digging.

23:34.150 --> 23:36.280
No. We make keys.

23:37.150 --> 23:38.190
What?

23:38.240 --> 23:39.850
Wait, wait. Listen.

23:39.900 --> 23:42.160
I measured the lock with
a pencil and drawing paper...

23:42.200 --> 23:44.850
You want to make a key with
pencil and drawing paper?

23:44.900 --> 23:46.380
No, no. From wood.

23:46.420 --> 23:49.340
Oh. You crazy. It break.

23:49.380 --> 23:50.950
It won't break
if you go against the grain.

23:50.990 --> 23:53.430
There's a reason
keys are made out of metal.

23:53.480 --> 23:55.660
I thought there was a first
for everything.

24:00.180 --> 24:01.920
OK.

24:01.960 --> 24:03.310
Where you get the wood from?

24:03.350 --> 24:06.220
- From the workshop.
- Heads up. Heads up.

24:10.230 --> 24:11.920
Three minutes.

24:14.060 --> 24:15.800
GUARD: Move along, you guys.

24:17.760 --> 24:19.450
Silence.

24:21.420 --> 24:23.810
Look at the keys
when he comes over.

24:23.850 --> 24:25.370
Watch closely.

24:25.420 --> 24:26.550
[CRASH!]

24:26.600 --> 24:29.390
No, no, no!
You have lost your mind!

24:29.420 --> 24:30.990
What are you talking about?!

24:31.030 --> 24:32.770
- VAN DER MERWE: What is this?
- Oh, nothing, meneer.

24:32.820 --> 24:34.300
No fighting.
We're just talking.

24:34.340 --> 24:35.820
VAN DER MERWE:
Not much peace and harmony

24:35.870 --> 24:37.920
among you white Mandelas, huh?

24:37.950 --> 24:39.300
No, no.

24:39.350 --> 24:40.880
Kaffir work.

24:43.000 --> 24:44.870
You're both confined
to your cell. Now!

24:44.920 --> 24:46.530
It's ridiculous.

24:46.570 --> 24:47.960
GUARD: Are you guys
gonna clean it up?

24:48.010 --> 24:50.840
Mongo here's gonna
look after you, eh?

24:54.280 --> 24:55.890
He didn't do anything.

24:55.930 --> 24:58.460
VAN DER MERWE:
You want to play with him? Ja?

24:59.370 --> 25:01.160
Then play still!

25:01.200 --> 25:03.850
Potluck! Get your black,
fat arse here now!

25:06.070 --> 25:07.510
Here!

25:07.550 --> 25:09.430
GUARD: Alright, guys,
move along.

25:09.460 --> 25:11.900
VAN DER MERWE:
Quiet! Quieten down!

25:12.820 --> 25:14.650
Be quiet!

25:14.690 --> 25:16.430
GUARD: You clean that up!

25:50.550 --> 25:52.380
GUARD: Next! Move it along!

25:54.340 --> 25:55.950
Next in line!

25:57.510 --> 26:00.680
OK, next prisoner!
Come on, move it!

26:02.820 --> 26:04.470
OK, next!

26:38.860 --> 26:41.600
[BELL RINGS]

26:41.640 --> 26:43.470
GUARD: Clear down!

27:17.240 --> 27:18.810
STEPHEN: [QUIETLY] Oh, shit!

27:18.850 --> 27:20.720
[GROANS] What an idiot.

27:24.690 --> 27:26.350
Halt!

27:32.870 --> 27:34.740
Just Lee.

27:34.780 --> 27:36.950
Everybody else clear down.

27:46.930 --> 27:48.540
File in!

27:55.720 --> 27:57.420
Here!

28:26.440 --> 28:28.880
You know, your look
is very intense, Jenkin.

28:28.920 --> 28:30.620
Sorry.

28:31.580 --> 28:33.150
"Sorry, MENEER."

28:33.190 --> 28:34.800
Sorry, meneer.

31:10.090 --> 31:12.050
[WHISPERS] Oh...

31:18.270 --> 31:20.930
So all we have to do
is make a really complex key...

31:20.970 --> 31:22.540
VAN DER MERWE: Silence.

31:24.010 --> 31:25.790
..is make a really complex key,

31:25.840 --> 31:28.270
then get it to reach a keyhole
on the other side

31:28.320 --> 31:30.490
of a steel-panel,
three-inch-thick iron door

31:30.540 --> 31:32.450
to which we have
totally no access?

31:35.110 --> 31:36.670
Total crazy.

31:37.720 --> 31:39.330
I love it.

31:54.300 --> 31:56.690
[SANDS KEY, BLOWS]

33:07.420 --> 33:09.340
- [GRUNTS]
- Ah, yes!

33:12.640 --> 33:14.860
Yes, yes!
[WHISPERS INDISTINCTLY]

33:18.470 --> 33:20.340
[GRUNTS]

33:22.040 --> 33:25.130
[TIM CONTINUES TRYING THE LOCK]

33:28.790 --> 33:29.930
- [SNAP!]
- Oh!

33:29.960 --> 33:31.660
No, no! No!

33:35.530 --> 33:37.100
Tim. Tim, Tim, Tim, Tim!

33:37.150 --> 33:38.890
Somebody's coming. Quick!

33:41.670 --> 33:43.280
[STEPHEN WHISTLES]

33:43.330 --> 33:46.200
[PANTS DESPERATELY]

33:46.240 --> 33:48.540
[WHISTLES]

33:52.120 --> 33:53.470
[GRUNTS]

33:54.950 --> 33:58.210
No, no. Come on, come out.
Come out. Get out.

33:58.250 --> 34:00.510
[WHISPERS] Tim! Tim!

34:00.560 --> 34:03.520
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

34:05.130 --> 34:06.530
Come on!

34:06.570 --> 34:09.180
[PANTS DESPERATELY]

34:32.810 --> 34:34.510
[GROANS]

34:51.920 --> 34:54.050
[DOOR UNLOCKS]

35:06.540 --> 35:07.980
[PANTS]

35:08.020 --> 35:10.770
[KEYS JANGLE,
FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

35:14.850 --> 35:16.810
[DOOR OPENS]

36:17.350 --> 36:20.440
[QUIET CONVERSATION]

36:27.750 --> 36:31.230
[SPEAKS FRENCH]

36:52.170 --> 36:54.700
Non. Non.

37:19.410 --> 37:20.970
[RAPS ON GLASS] Back off!

37:21.020 --> 37:22.670
What's the matter with you?
You are scaring him!

37:22.720 --> 37:25.030
Play still and lean away,
or I cut the children.

37:25.070 --> 37:26.600
What is wrong with you people?!

37:26.640 --> 37:29.510
OK. This session is terminated.
Get the woman in here.

37:29.550 --> 37:31.370
OK. OK, I'm s...I'm sorry.

37:31.420 --> 37:35.120
Get him out of here.
This session's over.

37:35.170 --> 37:37.350
Please. This is less than
30 minutes. Please. Please.

37:37.390 --> 37:39.610
- No, please! Please!
- Allez, viens, Antoine. Vite.

37:43.430 --> 37:45.040
Finished! It's finished!

37:49.400 --> 37:51.840
Enough of this French shit.
Get out! Now! Out!

37:54.970 --> 37:56.450
Papa!

37:56.490 --> 37:57.920
- Papa!
- Stop shouting.

37:57.970 --> 37:59.790
Papa! Papa!

38:02.060 --> 38:05.410
Get your...! Hey! Hey!

38:09.770 --> 38:11.990
- 17. Go!
- [TIM SPRINTS AWAY]

38:15.510 --> 38:18.550
[PANTS]

38:25.650 --> 38:27.300
STEPHEN: 15 seconds.

38:36.570 --> 38:38.830
How, uh...how is your son?

38:50.240 --> 38:53.150
OK. Let's go again.

38:55.030 --> 38:56.600
STEPHEN: Go!

38:58.810 --> 39:01.680
- TIM: He had a bad visit.
- Ja, I heard.

39:01.730 --> 39:04.820
And you?
How is your father doing?

39:05.780 --> 39:07.350
I don't know.

39:07.390 --> 39:09.400
He's sick.

39:10.700 --> 39:13.310
[SIGHS] We need
to get out of here.

39:15.480 --> 39:17.180
I think I have an idea.

39:20.490 --> 39:22.500
Antoine, he made me a kite.

39:24.010 --> 39:27.450
It has a small spindle
of fine black thread on it.

39:28.710 --> 39:32.630
I can tie the key at both ends,
put it across.

39:36.290 --> 39:38.030
Et voilÃ .

39:42.160 --> 39:44.550
I liked the pulley idea.

39:44.600 --> 39:46.610
Mmm.

39:46.640 --> 39:48.510
- No.
- What?

39:48.560 --> 39:54.740
If you can't turn it,
it's...just totally pointless.

39:54.780 --> 39:56.690
Totally pointless?

39:56.740 --> 39:58.350
OK.

39:59.660 --> 40:03.280
Well, what can take us
from this to this?

40:03.310 --> 40:06.140
That we have access to
from inside the cell.

40:06.190 --> 40:07.500
Exactly.

40:07.540 --> 40:09.370
TIM: You see, that's why
the string is smart.

40:09.410 --> 40:11.590
We can keep it here
and they'll never work out...

40:11.630 --> 40:13.760
Afternoon, meneer.

40:23.460 --> 40:25.070
What were you talking about?

40:25.120 --> 40:28.690
Nothing, meneer.
We were just talking.

40:28.730 --> 40:30.680
- Yeah.
- Sweeping, yeah?

40:30.730 --> 40:33.030
Clean cell, clean heart, meneer.

40:36.040 --> 40:37.730
Perhaps.

40:58.760 --> 41:00.890
[DOOR CLANGS SHUT]

41:05.290 --> 41:07.210
- OK, he's gone.
- How long was he there for?

41:07.250 --> 41:09.210
Did he hear us?
Did he hear anything?

41:09.250 --> 41:10.860
We weren't saying
anything incriminating.

41:10.900 --> 41:13.600
OK. OK, if he ask
question of us,

41:13.640 --> 41:16.470
we were just talking about...
we talk about string, huh?

41:16.520 --> 41:18.740
For how we hang up the broom.
Huh? That's it.

41:18.780 --> 41:21.210
- We forget everything else.
- Wait, wait, wait.

41:25.960 --> 41:28.440
Oh, yeah, yeah. Give it to me.

41:39.890 --> 41:41.460
Ha.

41:42.540 --> 41:44.150
Oh, yes.

41:44.200 --> 41:45.860
Oh!

41:45.890 --> 41:47.850
Going...

41:47.900 --> 41:49.340
You get it?

41:49.380 --> 41:51.380
- Not quite.
- Any more?

41:51.420 --> 41:53.200
[GRUNTS]

43:06.100 --> 43:07.750
[GRUNTS]

43:59.980 --> 44:01.590
- [LOCK CLICKS]
- [GRUNTS]

44:05.640 --> 44:07.200
[LOCK CLICKS]

44:36.930 --> 44:38.500
Oh, no.

44:38.550 --> 44:39.990
[GRUNTS]

44:41.460 --> 44:43.110
Shit!

44:46.640 --> 44:49.510
[DOOR CLANKS IN DISTANCE]

45:10.580 --> 45:12.760
[GRUNTS]

45:26.770 --> 45:28.600
[GRUNTS]

45:42.570 --> 45:44.140
OK. OK.

45:46.310 --> 45:47.970
[GRUNTS] Ja.

45:49.490 --> 45:51.230
[GROANS]

45:58.800 --> 46:00.370
[GROANS]

46:25.300 --> 46:27.480
[PANTS]

46:56.070 --> 46:57.460
So?

46:57.510 --> 46:58.940
Look.

46:58.990 --> 47:00.520
I have not slept all night.

47:00.560 --> 47:01.610
But you did it?

47:01.640 --> 47:04.950
- Mm-hm. Both doors.
- Really?

47:06.480 --> 47:09.400
You actually opened...
both the doors?

47:09.430 --> 47:11.080
Ja. I actually did.

47:14.050 --> 47:15.840
TrÃ¨s bien.

47:24.750 --> 47:26.360
STEPHEN: Rubbish?

47:31.540 --> 47:34.020
Nice work.

47:34.070 --> 47:36.340
Hey, we're not going to be able
to see it flower.

47:36.370 --> 47:38.980
[LOUD BANGING IN DISTANCE]

47:39.030 --> 47:41.080
That's the street outside.

47:42.030 --> 47:44.420
What the hell is that noise?

47:48.000 --> 47:49.650
Heads up.

48:03.530 --> 48:05.090
Hey!

48:26.470 --> 48:28.170
Shit.

48:44.230 --> 48:45.670
What was he doing here?

48:45.710 --> 48:48.100
Uh, he was fetching
my yard waste, meneer.

48:48.140 --> 48:51.050
Yeah, I saw that, cheese dick.
He's not on garden duty.

48:51.100 --> 48:53.530
Why is he collecting from you?
Why not him?

48:55.890 --> 48:57.500
From now on...

48:58.670 --> 49:00.930
..you clean up your own shit.

49:00.980 --> 49:02.670
Ja, meneer.

49:05.330 --> 49:07.160
[THUMP!]

49:14.690 --> 49:16.600
The captain has ordered
a crackdown.

49:16.650 --> 49:20.140
That's why they're all
so spooked.

49:20.170 --> 49:22.000
So, before you do
whatever it is you're doing,

49:22.050 --> 49:24.310
make sure you can get clear
of those snipers.

49:24.350 --> 49:27.390
- Ja. We're figuring it out.
- Yes, well, figure carefully.

49:27.440 --> 49:30.570
You fail, you'll get 25 years
if you're lucky.

49:30.620 --> 49:33.320
A bullet in the head
if you're not.

49:33.360 --> 49:36.840
The sniper on that gun walk
is a complete psychopath.

49:36.890 --> 49:38.940
I heard he shot some kids
in Joburg

49:38.980 --> 49:42.330
and they posted him here
to cool down.

49:42.370 --> 49:44.280
I'll keep looking out for you.

49:44.330 --> 49:47.080
But your whole plan
is doomed to failure.

49:47.110 --> 49:48.630
One of these mornings,

49:48.680 --> 49:50.680
I hope you're going to
wake up and see it.

49:57.520 --> 49:59.700
You're young. And I like you.

50:00.910 --> 50:03.650
But you're part of
a movement now.

50:03.700 --> 50:05.790
What you do affects everyone.

50:08.790 --> 50:10.620
Ja, so help us.

50:17.320 --> 50:18.890
[DOOR CREAKS]

50:59.970 --> 51:02.190
But if we can unlock three
doors, we can unlock 20...

51:02.230 --> 51:03.970
You don't even know
how many there are.

51:04.020 --> 51:05.330
It doesn't matter if it's 100.

51:05.370 --> 51:07.110
If they've got a lock,
we can make a key.

51:07.150 --> 51:08.840
Well, what about
the street outside?

51:08.890 --> 51:10.930
We need civilian clothes.
Other stuff. Quarters nearby.

51:10.980 --> 51:12.370
How do we get out
of the country?

51:12.420 --> 51:13.810
We are working on it.
One step at a time.

51:13.850 --> 51:15.150
MAN: There's too many unknowns!

51:15.200 --> 51:16.550
TIM: And we'll figure them out.
Be patient.

51:16.590 --> 51:18.770
Youneed to have patience
with us.

51:18.810 --> 51:20.990
Take patience from the others.
I'm not giving.

51:21.030 --> 51:23.160
20 years, I've been in here!

51:23.210 --> 51:27.080
And once a year,
they give me 30 minutes.

51:27.130 --> 51:31.140
30 minutes.
Alone with my own son.

51:32.870 --> 51:34.430
They try to break us.

51:35.830 --> 51:37.440
No more patience.

51:37.490 --> 51:39.270
We fight back!

51:41.880 --> 51:43.310
He's erratic.

51:43.360 --> 51:45.970
He's made a choice.
What about you?

51:46.020 --> 51:47.890
- Are you...
- Alright, listen!

51:53.810 --> 51:55.940
We are all on the same side.

51:59.380 --> 52:01.380
[DOOR OPENS]

52:03.080 --> 52:04.690
[DOOR CLOSES]

52:15.130 --> 52:18.960
TIM: In prison,
nothing stays the same,

52:19.010 --> 52:22.840
and yet nothing changes.

52:24.790 --> 52:29.710
The routine is the only thing
that gives time any meaning.

52:29.750 --> 52:31.840
So you use it.

52:31.890 --> 52:34.240
You use everything.

52:36.540 --> 52:39.760
You find the cracks
in their armour

52:39.810 --> 52:43.380
and you exploit them
to the fullest extent

52:43.420 --> 52:46.240
day after day after day.

53:17.760 --> 53:19.640
And through those cracks,

53:19.670 --> 53:23.460
in the uneventful footnotes
of prison life...

53:25.110 --> 53:27.110
..victory is won.

53:27.160 --> 53:30.160
That's how you beat
the fascists -

53:30.210 --> 53:33.480
one act of resistance
after another.

53:36.080 --> 53:37.690
- Kitson.
- How's it?

53:37.740 --> 53:39.960
Are you still in charge
of the movie closet?

53:40.000 --> 53:41.740
I'm going there tonight.

53:41.780 --> 53:43.560
When do they let you
have the key?

54:25.440 --> 54:27.970
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACH]

54:33.230 --> 54:34.840
Your order.

54:35.970 --> 54:37.540
Oh.

54:49.070 --> 54:50.770
Ja, I can see clearly now.

54:50.810 --> 54:52.420
Little prick.

54:53.860 --> 54:55.560
Ah! Potluck.

54:55.600 --> 54:58.780
That black little rat
you used to hang out with.

54:58.820 --> 55:01.260
Got stretched three days ago.

55:02.430 --> 55:05.220
I hear they had to
winch him up twice.

55:05.260 --> 55:07.740
Twitching and frothing
in his noose.

55:07.780 --> 55:09.430
Armed robbery,

55:09.480 --> 55:12.790
and he gets a free education
and statutory funeral.

55:12.830 --> 55:16.000
More than his worthless natives
could ever give to him, huh?

55:18.140 --> 55:19.700
Enjoy your glasses.

