1:02:25.520 --> 1:02:27.430
[WHISPERS]
Careful it doesn't break.

1:02:54.550 --> 1:02:56.460
[DISTANT COUGH]

1:02:59.780 --> 1:03:02.610
- That's enough. That's enough.
- Wait. Wait!

1:03:02.650 --> 1:03:04.920
That's enough.
Come on. Come on.

1:03:10.480 --> 1:03:12.780
[DISTANT VOICES]

1:03:26.590 --> 1:03:28.550
[LOCK CLANKS]

1:03:38.510 --> 1:03:40.330
[DOOR CLOSES]

1:03:45.560 --> 1:03:48.300
[SOFTLY]
Oh, for crying out loud!

1:03:48.350 --> 1:03:50.530
[GRUNTS]

1:03:57.960 --> 1:03:59.740
[WHISPERS]
Leave it. Leave it. Come on.

1:03:59.790 --> 1:04:01.790
Come on. Come on, come on!

1:04:10.540 --> 1:04:12.450
[PUFFS]

1:04:28.600 --> 1:04:30.690
[PANTS]

1:04:47.400 --> 1:04:49.270
Hmm.

1:05:17.300 --> 1:05:19.480
[GUARD'S SHOE SQUEAKS]

1:05:21.400 --> 1:05:23.970
[DOOR SQUEAKS, CLANKS]

1:05:25.310 --> 1:05:27.350
[LOCK CLICKS]

1:05:28.880 --> 1:05:31.180
[FOOTSTEPS RECEDE]

1:06:03.960 --> 1:06:06.140
[PANTS]

1:06:22.940 --> 1:06:24.990
[BIRDSONG]

1:06:25.020 --> 1:06:27.590
[DOOR CLANKS]

1:06:37.120 --> 1:06:39.860
[SNORING]

1:06:45.260 --> 1:06:47.000
GUARD: Stand outside your cell.

1:06:47.050 --> 1:06:48.710
[SNORTS]

1:07:01.450 --> 1:07:02.930
Are you sick, Jenkin?

1:07:02.980 --> 1:07:04.590
No, Captain.

1:07:04.630 --> 1:07:07.290
You have some sort of
auditory problem?

1:07:07.330 --> 1:07:08.900
Some infection or something?

1:07:08.940 --> 1:07:10.380
No, Captain.

1:07:10.420 --> 1:07:12.210
OK. OK.

1:07:12.250 --> 1:07:14.080
So the bell rang
and you heard it.

1:07:14.120 --> 1:07:15.730
Why didn't you wake up?

1:07:17.770 --> 1:07:19.290
I'm sorry, Captain.

1:07:19.340 --> 1:07:22.090
Oh, you're sorry? Oh, well,
that's touched my heart.

1:07:23.430 --> 1:07:24.860
Let me tell you something.

1:07:24.910 --> 1:07:27.520
When you hear the lunchtime bell
go this afternoon

1:07:27.560 --> 1:07:29.430
and you hear the suppertime bell
go this evening,

1:07:29.480 --> 1:07:30.790
you will remain in your cell

1:07:30.830 --> 1:07:32.570
and I'm not going to
give you any food.

1:07:32.610 --> 1:07:33.910
How does that sound, hmm?

1:07:33.960 --> 1:07:36.090
I'm...I'm terribly sorry,
Captain.

1:07:36.140 --> 1:07:39.060
Oh, terriblysorry now, is it?

1:07:39.100 --> 1:07:44.590
You joined a terrorist gang
of dirty black Rottweilers

1:07:44.630 --> 1:07:47.150
and they chewed you up
and they spat you out

1:07:47.190 --> 1:07:49.450
and now you're stuck in here
with me! Hmm?

1:07:49.500 --> 1:07:52.290
And 20 years' experience
in this job tells me

1:07:52.330 --> 1:07:54.730
you slept through my bed
because you're tired,

1:07:54.770 --> 1:07:58.430
and you're tired because
you're not sleeping, hmm?

1:07:58.470 --> 1:08:00.120
Why aren't you sleeping?

1:08:02.080 --> 1:08:03.870
I asked you a question.

1:08:05.250 --> 1:08:07.210
I-I'm sorry, Captain.

1:08:07.260 --> 1:08:09.660
Oh, "I'm sorry, Captain." Hmm.

1:08:09.690 --> 1:08:11.210
"I'm sorry, Captain."

1:08:11.260 --> 1:08:13.210
No, no, no, no. I can smell it.

1:08:14.310 --> 1:08:15.840
I'm sorry, Capt...

1:08:15.870 --> 1:08:19.220
[SHOUTS] Don't you ever
sleep through my bell again!

1:08:20.360 --> 1:08:21.540
Did you hear me
that time, Jenkin?

1:08:21.580 --> 1:08:23.450
- Ja, Captain.
- Mmm. That's good.

1:08:23.490 --> 1:08:25.920
OK, now, go and stand outside.
Go on. Go on.

1:08:28.840 --> 1:08:30.320
[GRUNTS]

1:08:31.240 --> 1:08:32.460
GUARD: No, stand there.

1:08:32.500 --> 1:08:34.200
Look at me
when I'm talking to you.

1:08:34.240 --> 1:08:36.020
LEONARD: Please. It's my son.

1:08:36.070 --> 1:08:38.860
[OBJECTS CLATTER]

1:08:38.900 --> 1:08:41.210
GUARD: Look at me when I'm
talking to you! Stand there!

1:08:41.250 --> 1:08:42.780
- LEONARD: Please...
- Don't bloody move!

1:08:42.810 --> 1:08:44.110
Please. It's of my son.

1:08:44.160 --> 1:08:46.290
I am allowed to have a picture.
It's of my son.

1:08:46.340 --> 1:08:48.910
No. No. No.
No, no, no, don't...

1:08:48.950 --> 1:08:50.820
[CLATTER, SHOUTING]

1:08:52.390 --> 1:08:53.920
Don't you touch them!

1:08:55.130 --> 1:08:57.820
- Do not touch me!
- On your knees, man!

1:08:57.870 --> 1:09:00.480
- No, no! No!
- Just shut up!

1:09:00.530 --> 1:09:02.840
They're mine! They're mine!

1:09:02.880 --> 1:09:04.410
They are mine!

1:09:04.440 --> 1:09:06.350
They are mine! You fascists!

1:09:06.400 --> 1:09:09.100
Fascists! They are mine,
you fascists!

1:09:09.140 --> 1:09:11.190
Don't touch them!
They are mine!

1:09:11.230 --> 1:09:13.840
[SCREAMS] They are mine!
They are mine!

1:09:13.890 --> 1:09:17.070
Don't you do it!
Don't you do it! They are mine!

1:09:17.110 --> 1:09:19.030
- They are mine!
- Shut up!

1:09:19.070 --> 1:09:20.550
They are mine! They are mine!

1:09:20.590 --> 1:09:22.760
No more of this dog shit
in here either! Huh?

1:09:24.330 --> 1:09:26.500
Hey! Jenkin! Here!

1:09:26.550 --> 1:09:29.860
LEONARD: [IN DISTANCE]
They are mine! They are mine!

1:09:29.900 --> 1:09:32.900
No more of that dog shit.
Is that clear?

1:09:32.950 --> 1:09:34.690
Ja, Captain.

1:09:39.310 --> 1:09:41.180
[OBJECTS CLATTER]

1:09:41.220 --> 1:09:42.830
Hmm?

1:09:48.400 --> 1:09:50.220
I'll never understand why
you people surround yourself

1:09:50.270 --> 1:09:52.530
with these stupid
little pictures.

1:09:53.930 --> 1:09:57.200
And you missed a visit, I hear.
Is that right?

1:09:57.240 --> 1:09:59.900
Ja, Captain. Illness.

1:09:59.930 --> 1:10:03.540
Oh, so, that's what they
tell you? [CHUCKLES]

1:10:03.590 --> 1:10:05.150
Hmm?

1:10:38.670 --> 1:10:40.200
What is this?

1:10:47.290 --> 1:10:48.600
It's...

1:10:50.120 --> 1:10:53.650
It's...it's...it's for...
um, photographs, Captain.

1:11:08.260 --> 1:11:10.830
What an utterly stupid idea.

1:11:14.880 --> 1:11:17.360
Yeah, you are quite the little
housewife, aren't you? Hey?

1:11:17.400 --> 1:11:18.970
Enough.

1:11:23.630 --> 1:11:25.020
There is something.

1:11:31.240 --> 1:11:33.500
There is something,
and I will find it.

1:11:36.770 --> 1:11:38.850
Now, you clean
all of that rubbish up.

1:11:42.990 --> 1:11:45.210
Huh? Another one?

1:11:46.210 --> 1:11:47.910
Alright, let's go.

1:11:51.130 --> 1:11:53.520
[PANTS HEAVILY]

1:12:04.410 --> 1:12:07.410
TIM: I buried my nerves
as deep as I possibly could.

1:12:10.410 --> 1:12:14.590
But what stays in
must come out.

1:12:14.630 --> 1:12:17.070
And the nightly panic attacks
grew more vicious

1:12:17.120 --> 1:12:18.900
as the days went on.

1:12:23.730 --> 1:12:29.430
And yet each obstacle presented new ways of seeing things.

1:12:29.480 --> 1:12:32.830
So the entire prison
became a hiding ground.

1:12:34.390 --> 1:12:36.000
Bookcases.

1:12:38.140 --> 1:12:41.100
Cracks in the wall.

1:12:41.140 --> 1:12:43.800
Laundry buckets
filled with soap powder.

1:12:45.530 --> 1:12:48.530
These became agents of freedom.

1:12:51.150 --> 1:12:54.290
And when one door closed,

1:12:54.330 --> 1:12:56.250
another one opened.

1:12:56.280 --> 1:12:57.630
[DOOR CREAKS]

1:12:59.290 --> 1:13:01.990
Many of them with keys
that I had made.

1:13:13.870 --> 1:13:15.960
Freedom is a very simple idea.

1:13:17.610 --> 1:13:21.090
Which is perhaps why
it can be so easily lost.

1:13:28.880 --> 1:13:30.440
Right.

1:13:34.450 --> 1:13:35.970
There's some decay here.

1:13:36.020 --> 1:13:38.070
Arggh! It's when
you touch the back.

1:13:38.110 --> 1:13:40.900
He'll have to come to my
surgery. It needs to come out.

1:13:44.550 --> 1:13:46.720
Not again, dammit!

1:13:50.250 --> 1:13:51.940
Stay!

1:13:57.870 --> 1:14:00.750
[THUMPS ON DOOR]
Loggie! The electric door!

1:14:00.780 --> 1:14:04.170
[THUMPS] We're standing here!

1:14:04.220 --> 1:14:07.870
Loggie! Open the grille door!
Push the button!

1:14:09.310 --> 1:14:12.880
[THUMPS] Open the damn door!
Loggie! Wake up!

1:14:12.930 --> 1:14:14.850
[DOOR WHIRRS]

1:14:14.880 --> 1:14:16.620
Oh! Well done!

1:14:20.110 --> 1:14:21.680
Right.

1:14:23.420 --> 1:14:24.810
Move!

1:14:24.850 --> 1:14:26.110
[GROANS]

1:14:26.160 --> 1:14:28.290
Oh, shit! Get on your feet, man!

1:14:35.430 --> 1:14:38.870
TIM: Over the past several
months, we've created 39 keys

1:14:38.910 --> 1:14:41.700
for 15 separate doors
around this prison.

1:14:41.740 --> 1:14:44.440
We've moved from our cells
to the corridor

1:14:44.480 --> 1:14:46.970
to downstairs
and into the admin section

1:14:47.000 --> 1:14:49.960
404 days without detection.

1:14:50.010 --> 1:14:52.190
We want to share this with you.

1:14:53.400 --> 1:14:55.140
Why won't you come?

1:14:55.190 --> 1:14:57.410
You said it yourself. They're
building a gun tower outside.

1:14:57.450 --> 1:15:00.070
- It's not operational yet.
- You think.

1:15:00.100 --> 1:15:02.280
Listen, running around
fiddling with cupboards

1:15:02.320 --> 1:15:05.190
and surviving out there
are two very different things.

1:15:05.240 --> 1:15:07.160
We're not going with you
because there's nowhere to go.

1:15:07.200 --> 1:15:09.940
We can go to Mozambique
and from there to Tanzania.

1:15:09.980 --> 1:15:11.240
You're not listening to us.

1:15:11.290 --> 1:15:12.900
I've had enough
of listening to you.

1:15:12.940 --> 1:15:14.590
- Hey! You show some respect!
- Why?

1:15:14.640 --> 1:15:16.250
Alright, that's enough!
I suggest that from now...

1:15:16.290 --> 1:15:18.030
And you,
we all know your decision

1:15:18.080 --> 1:15:19.870
to fly your flag from behind
your prison bars.

1:15:19.910 --> 1:15:22.610
- We don't agree.
- We should turn
and follow younow?

1:15:22.650 --> 1:15:24.960
- Follow your conscience.
- Are you my conscience?

1:15:25.000 --> 1:15:26.610
Yeah. If we have to be.

1:15:26.650 --> 1:15:28.650
Anything short of escape is
a pact with the devil himself.

1:15:28.700 --> 1:15:30.010
You know that!

1:15:30.050 --> 1:15:31.580
One by one,
this government is hacking

1:15:31.610 --> 1:15:32.870
everything we stand for
to pieces,

1:15:32.920 --> 1:15:34.670
and our inactivity
is complicity!

1:15:34.700 --> 1:15:37.050
Every day we sit here,
we justify this regime.

1:15:37.100 --> 1:15:40.500
But maybe all you white South
Africans are the same, huh?

1:15:40.540 --> 1:15:42.850
You're all talk. No action.

1:15:42.890 --> 1:15:45.110
- [SHOUTING]
- Hey, alright! Alright!

1:15:45.150 --> 1:15:46.590
Disrespectful son of a bitch!

1:15:46.630 --> 1:15:47.980
Remember who
you're talking to, boy!

1:15:48.020 --> 1:15:49.630
I know exactly
who I'm talking to.

1:15:49.680 --> 1:15:51.550
- Oh, is that right?
- Yes, it is!

1:15:51.590 --> 1:15:55.070
No action? You tell that
bullshit to Mandela! Or Sisulu!

1:15:55.120 --> 1:15:58.990
Or any of us at Rivonia! We did
everything we could in '64!

1:15:59.030 --> 1:16:02.680
I for one am proud to stand by
my brothers on Robben Island!

1:16:02.730 --> 1:16:04.950
Arrested together,
sentenced together,

1:16:04.990 --> 1:16:07.300
and if we have to,
we will die together.

1:16:07.350 --> 1:16:09.000
This is bullshit!

1:16:09.040 --> 1:16:10.820
They would escape, all of them!

1:16:10.870 --> 1:16:14.170
Only they can't, because
they don't have this weapon,
which we do.

1:16:14.220 --> 1:16:16.130
What we do have is our unity.

1:16:16.180 --> 1:16:18.190
As it is,
they will interrogate us,

1:16:18.230 --> 1:16:20.190
perhaps torture us for months,

1:16:20.230 --> 1:16:22.760
even years in here
because of you.

1:16:22.800 --> 1:16:24.240
So come with us.

1:16:24.280 --> 1:16:26.020
If you want to double
your sentence, go,

1:16:26.060 --> 1:16:28.020
but we are not coming with you,
not now.

1:16:28.060 --> 1:16:30.010
And don't you dare presume

1:16:30.060 --> 1:16:31.970
to come to my country
and tell me how things are!

1:16:32.020 --> 1:16:35.240
I've been in prison since before
you knew what apartheid was!

1:16:40.250 --> 1:16:42.340
I too have had to watch
my children grow up

1:16:42.380 --> 1:16:45.160
through that little
prison visitor window.

1:16:45.210 --> 1:16:49.000
I'm 15 years into
a four-life sentence.

1:16:49.040 --> 1:16:50.520
It doesn't get any easier.

1:16:50.560 --> 1:16:54.340
But a seed has to rot
in the ground

1:16:54.390 --> 1:16:57.690
before you can enjoy
the fruits of its tree.

1:16:57.740 --> 1:17:01.130
That is the price
we have to pay, all of us.

1:17:01.180 --> 1:17:04.050
- Rather than running away.
- We're not running away.

1:17:04.100 --> 1:17:07.240
- Then stay. Fight.
- This is how we fight.

1:17:08.410 --> 1:17:10.330
We can all go tonight.

1:17:11.370 --> 1:17:12.890
And when you're caught?

1:17:14.020 --> 1:17:15.760
LEONARD: When we're caught...

1:17:17.460 --> 1:17:19.900
..you can come back
from the dead

1:17:19.940 --> 1:17:23.380
for those brothers
that you are talking about.

1:17:23.420 --> 1:17:25.330
But you won't do it.

1:17:27.380 --> 1:17:30.120
I think you'll look back
at this moment

1:17:30.170 --> 1:17:34.870
and you'll regret this decision
for the rest of your lives.

1:17:46.050 --> 1:17:48.350
Come on. We tried.

1:17:54.890 --> 1:17:56.370
Merry Christmas.

1:17:57.500 --> 1:17:59.290
And to you.

1:18:49.120 --> 1:18:50.770
In.

1:18:59.390 --> 1:19:01.390
[TIM GASPS]

1:19:01.430 --> 1:19:02.990
[SOFTLY] Shit!

1:19:08.830 --> 1:19:10.350
I think it's too late

1:19:10.400 --> 1:19:12.620
to stop your vrot black teeth
falling out, huh?

1:19:13.880 --> 1:19:15.450
[SNIFFS]

1:19:15.490 --> 1:19:18.450
Or it's more kak to trade
with those black gorillas.

1:19:20.100 --> 1:19:22.100
Get them out! Now!

1:19:22.150 --> 1:19:24.330
Alright, Tooth Fairy. Out!

1:19:27.720 --> 1:19:29.730
Get out of my cell. Get out!

1:19:35.120 --> 1:19:37.600
[RUMMAGING]

1:19:38.640 --> 1:19:40.990
[CAPTAIN SHOUTS, GRUNTS]

1:19:43.560 --> 1:19:45.250
Ridiculous!

1:19:46.650 --> 1:19:49.870
I'm wasting my time in here!
Boy, I promise you!

1:19:49.920 --> 1:19:51.920
[BELL RINGS]

1:19:51.960 --> 1:19:53.650
[DOOR LOCKS]

1:20:08.060 --> 1:20:09.890
[MUTTERS] Oh, thank God!

1:20:26.520 --> 1:20:28.090
Ah!

1:20:39.180 --> 1:20:40.960
Aha.

1:20:52.150 --> 1:20:55.190
[GUARDS CHATTER AND LAUGH]

1:20:57.030 --> 1:20:58.860
GUARD: Crying like
a little girl.

1:21:06.080 --> 1:21:08.300
[GUARDS LAUGH, CHATTER]

1:21:10.650 --> 1:21:12.570
[LOCK CLANKS]

1:21:38.410 --> 1:21:40.240
[BELLY RUMBLES]

1:21:49.300 --> 1:21:51.300
MAN: [WHISPERS]
Good luck, you guys.

1:21:51.340 --> 1:21:52.990
[DOOR CLANKS]

1:21:58.000 --> 1:21:59.830
It's not too late to come.

1:22:01.350 --> 1:22:04.700
Make damn sure you get clear.
You hear me?

1:22:11.230 --> 1:22:13.360
[SIGHS]

1:22:40.780 --> 1:22:42.210
[GROANS]

1:22:46.000 --> 1:22:47.700
[WHISPERS] Come on,
come on, come on.

1:23:18.820 --> 1:23:20.430
Mm-hm.

1:23:34.880 --> 1:23:37.020
Hmm.

1:23:37.060 --> 1:23:40.410
[MUTTERS] How can they
find anything in here?

1:24:05.430 --> 1:24:07.430
[METAL CLINKS]

1:24:07.480 --> 1:24:09.530
[GROANS]

1:24:21.930 --> 1:24:23.410
[GUARD COUGHS]

1:24:23.450 --> 1:24:25.720
[SLOW FOOTSTEPS]

1:24:25.760 --> 1:24:29.590
- Wait.
- [CLOSET DOOR SQUEAKS SHUT]

1:24:31.330 --> 1:24:33.770
[GUARD LOCKS CLOSET]

1:24:35.640 --> 1:24:38.030
[SLOW FOOTSTEPS, GRUNTING]

1:24:39.770 --> 1:24:41.850
[DOOR CLOSES]

1:24:41.900 --> 1:24:44.250
[LOCK CLANKS]

1:24:47.950 --> 1:24:50.210
[UNLOCKS DOOR]

1:25:02.010 --> 1:25:04.580
[GUARD GRUNTS, STRAINS]

1:25:12.450 --> 1:25:14.150
What's this?

1:25:14.200 --> 1:25:15.940
[TOILET FLUSHES]

1:25:19.720 --> 1:25:21.460
Go. Go, go. Go.

1:25:22.900 --> 1:25:24.680
Where's the paperclip?
The paperclip?

1:25:24.730 --> 1:25:26.690
- Where is it?
- It must be here.

1:25:26.730 --> 1:25:28.870
Just bloody pull it!

1:25:37.870 --> 1:25:39.520
[KEYS JANGLE]

1:25:39.570 --> 1:25:41.270
[SIGHS]

1:25:45.660 --> 1:25:47.660
[GROANS]

1:26:08.900 --> 1:26:10.550
[GROANS]

1:26:12.650 --> 1:26:15.960
Meneer! Meneer!
I'm calling you!

1:26:16.000 --> 1:26:18.050
Meneer! Meneer!

1:26:18.090 --> 1:26:19.350
[SIGHS]

1:26:19.390 --> 1:26:21.080
Meneer!

1:26:21.130 --> 1:26:24.170
OTHERS: Meneer! Meneer!

1:26:24.220 --> 1:26:26.220
[SIGHS]

1:26:26.270 --> 1:26:29.450
[PRISONERS CALL OUT]

1:26:35.620 --> 1:26:38.800
Alright, alright! Enough!

1:27:44.960 --> 1:27:46.140
- Stop.
- What?

1:27:46.170 --> 1:27:48.300
I need to go back.
I need to go back.

1:27:48.350 --> 1:27:49.920
- Why?
- For the buzzer.

1:27:49.960 --> 1:27:52.170
The buzzer for
the electric door.

1:27:59.670 --> 1:28:01.240
Nice.

1:28:04.540 --> 1:28:06.110
[DOOR WHIRRS]

1:28:06.150 --> 1:28:07.540
Yes!

1:28:09.590 --> 1:28:11.120
Come on!

1:28:16.070 --> 1:28:17.500
Come on, come on, come, come.

1:28:17.550 --> 1:28:18.770
Alright.

1:28:18.810 --> 1:28:20.550
Come on, come on, come on.

1:28:26.300 --> 1:28:28.520
- [LOCK CLANKS]
- OK. Go.

1:28:33.090 --> 1:28:35.300
OK. Workshop key.

1:28:39.100 --> 1:28:40.360
Round tip.

1:28:40.400 --> 1:28:42.960
Just the workshop key.

1:28:43.010 --> 1:28:44.840
Visitor's room.
It's a round tip.

1:28:44.880 --> 1:28:46.400
No, it's not. That's not
what we need right now.

1:28:46.450 --> 1:28:50.280
- It's a round tip.
- Guys! Just try them both.

1:28:58.900 --> 1:29:00.300
No.

1:29:00.330 --> 1:29:01.720
See?

1:29:03.730 --> 1:29:04.950
Thank you.

1:29:05.990 --> 1:29:08.030
[DISTANT BANG]

1:29:10.520 --> 1:29:12.000
It's OK. Go on, go on, go on.

1:29:17.350 --> 1:29:18.910
Get out the way.

1:29:22.970 --> 1:29:25.410
- [LOCK CLUNKS]
- Ah!

1:29:28.670 --> 1:29:30.630
Come on, come on. Come, come.

1:29:30.670 --> 1:29:33.940
You have to push it
all the way in, mon ami.

1:29:47.730 --> 1:29:50.260
[LAUGHS]

1:29:51.260 --> 1:29:52.700
The gates are wide open.

1:29:52.730 --> 1:29:54.780
You can see the street.

1:29:56.390 --> 1:29:58.080
Oh, we made it.

1:30:02.570 --> 1:30:04.090
My God.

1:30:08.400 --> 1:30:10.570
I'll never forget this moment.

1:30:15.630 --> 1:30:18.590
- OK.
- OK. OK.

1:30:24.380 --> 1:30:26.820
[TRIES KEY]

1:30:26.860 --> 1:30:28.430
OK. Next.

1:30:29.510 --> 1:30:31.590
[TRIES KEY]

1:30:36.910 --> 1:30:38.920
[TRIES KEY]

1:30:42.040 --> 1:30:43.610
Next.

1:30:48.530 --> 1:30:50.150
Next.

1:30:51.580 --> 1:30:53.150
- You push it all the way in?
- Yes!

1:30:53.190 --> 1:30:54.800
Yes, I'm pushing it
all the way in.

1:30:54.840 --> 1:30:56.530
Just give me another one.

1:30:56.580 --> 1:30:58.140
I'm out.

1:30:59.890 --> 1:31:01.850
That's the last one we have.

1:31:05.590 --> 1:31:07.670
[TRIES KEY]

1:31:10.510 --> 1:31:12.080
[GROANS]

1:31:18.730 --> 1:31:21.340
[ROARS]

1:31:21.390 --> 1:31:24.700
- What are we going to do?
- Well...we have to go back.

1:31:24.740 --> 1:31:26.530
Back? I'd rather be shot.

1:31:26.570 --> 1:31:28.140
Well, we don't have
any other choice!

1:31:28.180 --> 1:31:30.450
Hey, guys, just wait. OK, wait.

1:31:34.400 --> 1:31:35.960
[KNOCKS]

1:31:40.100 --> 1:31:41.710
Ja, maybe.

1:31:44.800 --> 1:31:46.370
- What?
- Chisel.

1:31:46.410 --> 1:31:48.500
What's going on?
What are you doing?

1:31:49.420 --> 1:31:50.860
No!

1:31:50.900 --> 1:31:53.820
No! No! Stop! Stop!

1:31:53.860 --> 1:31:55.250
Leonard!

1:31:55.290 --> 1:31:57.160
This is gonna get us caught!

1:31:58.380 --> 1:32:00.550
And they're gonna know
that we did it!

1:32:00.600 --> 1:32:03.120
Screwdriver.
I need to get in deeper.

1:32:06.260 --> 1:32:08.090
[BANGING]

1:32:14.660 --> 1:32:16.100
You can hear it
in the bloody corridor!

1:32:16.140 --> 1:32:17.750
- [GRUNTS]
- Time to have a look.

1:32:17.790 --> 1:32:20.660
See? It's coming.

1:32:23.060 --> 1:32:24.630
It's getting close.

1:32:26.850 --> 1:32:29.290
Ja. OK, ja.
Give me the screwdriver.

1:32:29.330 --> 1:32:30.940
Come on, keep going.

1:32:53.220 --> 1:32:54.790
Hold. Hold. Hold.

1:33:04.800 --> 1:33:08.500
Alright, alright.
That's enough. That's enough.

1:33:16.290 --> 1:33:17.730
VoilÃ .

1:33:17.770 --> 1:33:19.510
OK. Let's go.

1:33:30.780 --> 1:33:32.260
OK?

1:33:32.300 --> 1:33:35.130
- Ja, ja.
- OK.

1:33:35.170 --> 1:33:36.950
OK. No, no, no. Wait, wait.

1:33:42.310 --> 1:33:44.090
What...?

1:33:47.530 --> 1:33:49.360
OK. Let's go.

1:33:49.410 --> 1:33:51.020
OK. Guys, I just want
to tell you, there's no...

1:33:51.060 --> 1:33:53.720
Tim, just open the damn door!

1:34:11.430 --> 1:34:13.300
[QUIETLY] No! No! Wait! No!

1:34:19.220 --> 1:34:20.790
Right.

1:34:21.740 --> 1:34:24.130
See?

1:34:24.180 --> 1:34:25.750
- Oh, man.
- Let me see.

1:34:33.150 --> 1:34:34.800
OK, he's going...

1:34:37.060 --> 1:34:38.580
..he's going...

1:34:40.200 --> 1:34:41.850
Go. Go. Go.

1:34:48.900 --> 1:34:51.380
[BREATHES HEAVILY]

1:34:52.600 --> 1:34:55.170
[ENGINE STARTS]

1:35:03.650 --> 1:35:06.090
The map. Give me the map.

1:35:16.670 --> 1:35:18.370
Go.

1:35:26.460 --> 1:35:28.380
Go. Go.

1:36:00.100 --> 1:36:02.580
[MEN CONVERSE INDISTINCTLY]

1:36:12.370 --> 1:36:14.680
[TRAIN WHEELS SQUEAL]

1:36:31.920 --> 1:36:34.310
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

1:36:35.350 --> 1:36:37.480
- Alright. Alright.
- Go. Come on.

